{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf139213-266f-4779-9351-2541b3ee90f2","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_D6itB8YovquVC3aBKqzmIz","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-86fcab26fa9e41cd9d47f2bb4269d41f"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-86fcab26fa9e41cd9d47f2bb4269d41f."}],"interactionId":"b2c21967-2145-43f7-a20d-dd0060a3ff1a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review the template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. Let me check what's required and what might be missing or problematic.\n\nKey things to check for a dotnet template:\n1. `$schema` - recommended for validation\n2. `identity` - present ✓\n3. `name` - present ✓\n4. `shortName` - present ✓\n5. `author` - present ✓\n6. `classifications` - present ✓\n7. `tags` - present with language and type ✓\n8. `sourceName` - present ✓\n9. `preferNameDirectory` - optional but recommended\n\n\n10. `defaultName` - optional but nice to have\n11. `groupIdentity` - recommended for NuGet\n12. `precedence` - useful when multiple versions exist\n\nThe template is mostly functional but missing a few key fields for NuGet publishing: no `$schema` for validation, no `groupIdentity` to organize related templates, and `preferNameDirectory` should be set to true for project templates. The Framework default is set to `net9.0` which might feel outdated by 2026, and there's no description field either.\n\nI should also check whether there's a description field at the top level for discoverability, and whether postActions are defined for any setup steps. Let me look for the packaging files like .nupkg or .csproj to see how this is being distributed.","outputTokens":440},"id":"873c474d-c8c0-4cdd-b98b-9ce519582908","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:42:40.917Z","parentId":"8d02fb04-fb48-4789-a87e-4d205d2ecd53"}
